      <odd id="aspace_ed777d0e02011dfd0576b7c62fe7503d">
         <head>General note</head>
         <p>Forms part of Yale Record Group 46-A (YRG 46-A), Records and materials broadly documenting Yale buildings, facilities, and grounds.</p>  
      </odd>
      <prefercite id="aspace_df797551a6a2b22fafb346266956b792">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Pach Brothers Photographs of Yale and New Haven (RU 644). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_0d21ca99b006c1dbb372b23022503d8a">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>The materials are open for research.</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
      <arrangement id="aspace_4e148aa8006fb75eb87c21b361e9895a">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The materials are arranged by subject.</p>  
      </arrangement>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_7e8ec5fc6702fb7ea25b18a6ddc7739f">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The collection is comprised of photographs of various Yale University academic buildings and New Haven, Connecticut scenes. The photographs were taken by Pach Brothers, the official university photographers for many of the late nineteenth-century Yale class albums.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
